46:27.279 --> 46:28.681
Different week, different house.

46:28.715 --> 46:32.351
Different mommy,
different daddy.

46:32.384 --> 46:35.020
Same bruises.

46:35.053 --> 46:40.092
You heading west?

46:40.125 --> 46:44.029
Mhm, no, no, no.

46:44.062 --> 46:48.333
There's a big difference
between a runner and a killer.

46:48.367 --> 46:54.072
You don't want to
cross that line.

46:54.106 --> 46:56.442
Look, I can take you as far as
Delta County, Colorado.

46:56.475 --> 46:58.110
We've got business there.

46:58.143 --> 47:03.182
Drop you off at Raton,
find you something there.

47:03.215 --> 47:06.518
I'm not supposed to
talk to strangers.

47:06.552 --> 47:09.421
That hurts my feelings.

47:09.455 --> 47:11.691
Strangers?

47:11.724 --> 47:17.229
Honey, we ain't strangers
to calling bruises birthmarks.

47:17.262 --> 47:20.432
Let me show you something.

47:30.442 --> 47:32.211
Go on, take a look.

47:39.151 --> 47:44.791
Let's not worry about...

47:44.824 --> 47:46.558
Ugh!

47:46.592 --> 47:50.429
Ugh.

47:57.269 --> 48:00.339
She a little young, Pete.

48:00.372 --> 48:01.340
Mm.

49:22.855 --> 49:29.762
Jo.

49:29.796 --> 49:31.864
Josephine, come here.

49:45.745 --> 49:49.481
Jo.

49:49.514 --> 49:51.483
Come on.

50:59.719 --> 51:01.921
- Are you okay?
- Sh, stay there.

51:01.954 --> 51:06.458
Just trust me.

52:05.550 --> 52:07.954
Hey, Nicky, keep an eye
on the girl, all right?

53:29.802 --> 53:32.805
Are you my guardian angel?

53:34.106 --> 53:35.908
Yes.

53:45.117 --> 53:48.988
You know,
I dated this girl once,

53:49.021 --> 53:52.091
and... well,
I didn't really date her,

53:52.124 --> 53:53.826
like, we went on a few dates,

53:53.860 --> 53:55.627
and they were nice dates,

53:55.661 --> 53:59.165
and I really thought
we were gonna stick it out,

53:59.198 --> 54:01.801
and then she told me,

54:01.834 --> 54:04.670
"You're too short."

54:04.704 --> 54:07.039
Is there a gun around?

54:07.073 --> 54:08.406
Yeah.

54:08.440 --> 54:10.475
Right in there.

54:11.911 --> 54:14.412
I'm too short?

54:14.446 --> 54:16.682
You're too tall!

54:20.686 --> 54:23.823
Can you see the future?

54:23.856 --> 54:26.792
Do I ever get married?

54:27.960 --> 54:30.897
I hope I marry Margot Robbie.

54:30.930 --> 54:33.065
She'd be my first pick.

54:33.099 --> 54:37.703
But if I could go back,
it'd be Marisa Tomei.

54:37.737 --> 54:40.572
But I really want
to have kids.

54:40.605 --> 54:43.575
Like six or seven kids.

54:43.608 --> 54:45.144
Probably seven kids.

54:45.177 --> 54:50.182
- Like, I date her now...
- Show me the nearest town.

54:50.216 --> 54:53.052
Uh...

54:53.085 --> 54:54.854
Bingo.

54:54.887 --> 54:57.857
And this.

54:57.890 --> 54:59.158
That?

55:01.961 --> 55:04.130
Half a mile

55:04.163 --> 55:06.098
that way.

55:06.132 --> 55:09.068
It would work.

55:09.101 --> 55:11.837
But I really want
to have kids.

55:13.973 --> 55:15.540
Yeah.

55:16.842 --> 55:18.510
Come on.

55:25.785 --> 55:28.486
We can't leave her.

55:28.520 --> 55:32.124
If she didn't want to stay here,
she would've left by now.

55:34.160 --> 55:35.828
I'll leave you too.

55:35.861 --> 55:38.030
You said nobody ever stuck
their neck out for you.

55:38.064 --> 55:40.633
Well, she did,
and if we leave now,

55:40.666 --> 55:42.702
we're no better than them.

57:40.252 --> 57:42.620
Where's my popcorn?

1:02:56.135 --> 1:02:58.604
What will we do if she...

1:05:58.617 --> 1:05:59.819
Jo!

1:06:01.453 --> 1:06:03.522
Jo!

1:06:16.903 --> 1:06:18.705
There's a lot of blood.

1:06:23.876 --> 1:06:27.546
Help! Help!

1:06:27.579 --> 1:06:30.215
Help!

1:06:33.619 --> 1:06:35.822
Anybody, please!

1:06:35.855 --> 1:06:38.290
Our Father,

1:06:38.323 --> 1:06:40.192
who art in heaven,

1:06:40.225 --> 1:06:41.426
hallowed be Thy name...

1:06:41.460 --> 1:06:43.630
- Help!
- Thy kingdom come;

1:06:43.663 --> 1:06:48.367
Thy will be done
on earth as it is in heaven.

1:06:48.400 --> 1:06:49.869
Give us this day
our daily bread...

1:06:49.902 --> 1:06:51.303
Help...

1:06:51.336 --> 1:06:53.171
...and forgive us
our trespasses.

1:06:54.272 --> 1:06:55.440
Please.

1:06:55.474 --> 1:06:56.943
Help!

1:07:06.753 --> 1:07:08.220
Help!

1:09:21.453 --> 1:09:26.625
♪ Deep river ♪

1:09:26.659 --> 1:09:34.634
♪ My home is over Jordan ♪

1:09:34.667 --> 1:09:39.872
♪ Deep river ♪

1:09:39.906 --> 1:09:43.843
♪ I want to cross ♪

1:09:43.876 --> 1:09:50.382
♪ I want to cross over
into campground ♪

1:13:27.299 --> 1:13:30.568
I ain't never seen Him
up there like that.

1:13:34.807 --> 1:13:36.909
He looks so sad.

1:14:40.139 --> 1:14:42.675
Oh, all right, all right!

1:14:47.713 --> 1:14:49.748
Oh...

1:14:49.782 --> 1:14:52.251
What a strange place this is,
you know?

1:14:55.454 --> 1:14:58.257
Vegas will always be, uh,

1:14:58.290 --> 1:15:02.027
kind of a magic for me.

1:15:02.061 --> 1:15:05.064
My first and only love,

1:15:05.097 --> 1:15:08.000
I think, was conceived here.

1:15:09.401 --> 1:15:11.070
Um...

1:15:11.103 --> 1:15:14.240
This girl in a blue dress
bought me a drink.

1:15:14.273 --> 1:15:16.876
When I asked her why,
she said,

1:15:16.909 --> 1:15:20.246
"A good life is filled
with people you did right by,

1:15:20.279 --> 1:15:23.048
and you need a drink, right?"

1:15:23.082 --> 1:15:25.217
She knew. She always knew.

1:15:27.052 --> 1:15:28.888
Didn't end up
doing right by her,

1:15:28.921 --> 1:15:31.423
but she sure did right by me.

1:16:25.778 --> 1:16:27.746
Is that the Eiffel Tower?

1:16:32.418 --> 1:16:35.120
It's a lot smaller
than I thought.

1:18:41.947 --> 1:18:42.948
Thanks.

1:21:43.095 --> 1:21:44.496
Shoes.

1:21:50.770 --> 1:21:52.371
Do you think he got fat?

1:21:52.404 --> 1:21:54.106
He's not gonna be fat!

1:21:54.139 --> 1:21:55.240
Maybe he went bald.

1:21:55.274 --> 1:21:56.341
He's not!

1:21:56.375 --> 1:21:58.778
He's gonna be the opposite.

1:22:17.797 --> 1:22:20.098
Can I help you?

1:22:22.401 --> 1:22:25.070
Have you seen Johnny Alvarez?

1:22:28.240 --> 1:22:30.175
They, uh...

1:22:30.208 --> 1:22:32.578
They broke up a few years back.

1:22:32.611 --> 1:22:34.613
I haven't seen Johnny in...

1:22:36.683 --> 1:22:39.251
- Yeah, I got nothing for you.
- Do you got a number?

1:22:39.284 --> 1:22:41.353
- No.
- An address?

1:22:41.386 --> 1:22:43.522
Look, I got a lot of things
I gotta get done today.

1:22:43.555 --> 1:22:45.223
I don't have time
for a Johnny Alvarez groupie...

1:22:45.257 --> 1:22:47.292
He's my dad.

1:22:49.328 --> 1:22:51.196
Oh, uh...

1:22:55.334 --> 1:22:56.836
Let me check, but...

1:22:56.869 --> 1:23:00.707
Johnny's more of kind of
a stay-at-home, uh...

1:23:00.740 --> 1:23:03.442
He doesn't get out that much.

1:23:26.833 --> 1:23:28.835
Do I look okay?

1:23:28.868 --> 1:23:30.602
You're beautiful.

1:23:30.637 --> 1:23:33.840
Besides, I'll be right here.

1:24:26.693 --> 1:24:28.226
Yeah, I'm comin'.

1:24:28.260 --> 1:24:30.328
Yeah.

1:24:30.362 --> 1:24:31.496
What?

1:24:38.971 --> 1:24:41.473
You selling cooking
or something?

1:24:41.506 --> 1:24:43.876
- I just found this...
- I don't want any cookies.

1:24:45.978 --> 1:24:49.214
Oh, I just found this.

1:24:54.386 --> 1:24:55.487
Got a pen?

1:24:57.023 --> 1:24:58.858
No.

1:25:00.960 --> 1:25:02.360
You want an autograph,

1:25:02.394 --> 1:25:06.231
but you don't bring
something to write with.

1:25:10.937 --> 1:25:14.006
I got one inside,
meet me around back.

1:25:45.470 --> 1:25:48.373
What're you doin'
with a backpack that big?

1:25:50.342 --> 1:25:51.978
Big backpack.

1:26:46.531 --> 1:26:50.368
- Name?
- Jo, Jo Frost.

1:26:52.537 --> 1:26:55.775
- Where you from?
- Virginia.

1:26:55.808 --> 1:26:57.977
Long way.

1:27:01.647 --> 1:27:02.882
Where's your mama?

1:27:09.755 --> 1:27:11.691
Ain't got a mama.

1:27:14.626 --> 1:27:16.128
Everybody's got a mama.

1:28:15.821 --> 1:28:18.724
She said your voice was so soft,
it sounded like

1:28:18.758 --> 1:28:21.827
you stole it from an angel
when he was dozin'.

1:28:23.595 --> 1:28:27.733
That sounds like the kind
of sappy crap she'd say.

1:28:43.916 --> 1:28:45.785
Where's your daddy?

1:28:52.692 --> 1:28:55.227
Thought you could tell me that.

1:29:14.246 --> 1:29:17.582
This is the fella
you're lookin' for.

1:29:23.022 --> 1:29:25.992
Those ain't my eyes.

1:29:33.833 --> 1:29:36.002
You got your mama's eyes.

1:29:44.076 --> 1:29:45.644
She said

1:29:45.678 --> 1:29:49.614
she never loved a boy
as much as Johnny Alvarez.

1:29:51.183 --> 1:29:54.720
She wasn't lyin'.

1:29:57.289 --> 1:29:59.591
Your ma had a big heart.

1:30:04.096 --> 1:30:05.264
The biggest.

1:30:08.234 --> 1:30:10.102
But it's too big for just me.

1:30:19.311 --> 1:30:21.080
Did you love her?

1:30:22.248 --> 1:30:25.017
You love every Julia at 18.

1:30:36.796 --> 1:30:38.931
Can I stay with you?

1:33:07.947 --> 1:33:10.749
Always wanted
to see the ocean.

1:34:03.836 --> 1:34:05.204
Ain't you comin'?

1:34:10.609 --> 1:34:13.045
You're 11 years old now.

1:34:13.078 --> 1:34:15.047
It's time.

1:34:15.080 --> 1:34:18.284
I'm only 10 and a half.

1:34:28.994 --> 1:34:32.398
You'll make new friends.

1:34:32.431 --> 1:34:34.466
Have you met me?

1:34:44.576 --> 1:34:47.279
If you go in there
and really be yourself,

1:34:47.313 --> 1:34:50.549
then they'll be racing
to be your best friend.

1:34:53.118 --> 1:34:54.987
No, they won't.

1:34:55.020 --> 1:34:57.156
They ain't nothin' like you.

1:35:01.293 --> 1:35:04.463
There's things I can't give you,
things you need,

1:35:04.496 --> 1:35:07.066
things I want you to have,

1:35:07.099 --> 1:35:09.301
instead of getting in the way.

1:35:15.307 --> 1:35:19.078
You may not have a home,
but you can be a home.

1:35:24.983 --> 1:35:29.388
Besides, I'll be right here!

1:35:50.042 --> 1:35:54.113
Young lady, what are you doing
out here all by yourself?

1:37:27.072 --> 1:37:29.408
I like you.

1:37:29.441 --> 1:37:31.711
What's your name?

1:37:31.744 --> 1:37:33.713
Josephine.

1:37:33.746 --> 1:37:36.683
I'll call you Jo, cool?

1:37:36.716 --> 1:37:40.586
No, call me my name or nothing.

1:37:40.619 --> 1:37:41.721
Cool.

1:37:41.754 --> 1:37:44.022
- Cool.
- Cool.
